description:
RE-VERIFIED 2026-06-14 (rad v0.10.1): still reproduces.

`\{` correctly produces a literal `{` to prevent interpolation, but `\}` does NOT produce a literal `}` - it produces the literal two characters `\}`.

**Repro:**
print("\{ and \}")
// Expected: { and }
// Actual:   { and \}   (the \} stays as backslash-brace)

Minor inconsistency but surprising when users discover it.

**Fix (slam dunk):** add a `\}` escape handler mirroring `\{` (around rts/converter.go:1338). Pure symmetry, low risk.
